.TH "alloc_chrdev_region" 9 "alloc_chrdev_region" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
alloc_chrdev_region \- register a range of char device numbers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" alloc_chrdev_region
.BI "(dev_t *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned baseminor "  ","
.BI "unsigned count "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
output parameter for first assigned number
.IP "baseminor" 12
first of the requested range of minor numbers
.IP "count" 12
the number of minor numbers required
.IP "name" 12
the name of the associated device or driver
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates a range of char device numbers.  The major number will be
chosen dynamically, and returned (along with the first minor number)
in \fIdev\fP.  Returns zero or a negative error code.
